Thus, the new element first gets a temporary name, with symbol consisting of three letters.", "fibs": ["Table"]}
{"text": "Later permanent name and symbol are given by a vote of IUPAC representatives from each country.", "fibs": ["name"]}
{"text": "The permanent name might reflect the country (or state of the country) in which the element was discovered, or pay tribute to a notable scientist.", "fibs": ["name"]}
{"text": "Official names of all elements have been announced by IUPAC.", "fibs": ["IUPAC"]}
